00:39:02.330 --> 00:39:06.620
Because when you start thinking
about, I want to move

00:39:06.620 --> 00:39:15.960
this div, for example, over 600
pixels, on a mobile device

00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:18.030
that's maybe only
320 pixels wide.

00:39:18.030 --> 00:39:19.620
You're going to move
it off screen.

00:39:19.620 --> 00:39:24.260
So as you think about using
absolute and relative

00:39:24.260 --> 00:39:27.430
positioning, you need to be very
careful that you're not

00:39:27.430 --> 00:39:32.910
using pixels, but instead of
using either percents or--

00:39:32.910 --> 00:39:35.910
there's a new unit that
you can use--

00:39:35.910 --> 00:39:37.490
I don't think it's landed
everywhere.

00:39:37.490 --> 00:39:40.600
I think it's only landed
